title: [Bug]: When we use MSBuildLocator.RegisterDefaults(); the command "dotnet build" DOES NOT return the correct message when called from Powershell

nodes.body:
Hi @garevaul,

Thank you for providing the details.
Could you explain why you need to use both `dotnet build `& `MSBuildLocator.RegisterDefaults();`?
In fact, you don't need to call MSBuildLocator, if you decide to call MSBuild using `dotnet build ` command.

Hi @YuliiaKovalova 

I have my build code in a Net6.0 Winforms Application. There the need is to build a .Net Framework 4.8 project and also couple of .Net 6.0 projects.

So one option is that I could use MSBuild.exe for All.

But I want to use 'dotnet build' for building all the .Net 6.0 projects, because it is fast, and returns concise messages.

But I cannot use 'dotnet build' for building the framework 4.8 project.

So I need to use both 'MSBuild' and 'dotnet build' within my Application.

Hi @YuliiaKovalova @rainersigwald 

Also, we need to use `MSBuildLocator.RegisterDefaults();` when we need to use the code (given below) in the same project where we want to use the PowerShell 'dotnet build', because these Classes are from 'Microsoft.Build 17.3.2 nuget'.

`ProjectRootElement projectRootElement = ProjectRootElement.Open("D:\\Abc.csproj");`

@garevaul

Hi @YuliiaKovalova @rainersigwald 

Also, when we use `MSBuildLocator.RegisterDefaults();`, then even when we do 'dotnet clean' in PowerShell (!! FROM C# !!),
